18 (2) the items described in subsection (a)(1) through (a)(4).
19 (d) Upon request, the division shall provide to an individual in need
20 of self-directed in-home care the following:
21 (1) Without charge, a list of personal services attendants who are
22 registered with the division and available within the requested
23 geographic area.
24 (2) A copy of the information of a specified personal services
25 attendant who is on file with the division under subsection (c).
26 The division may charge a fee for shipping, handling, and copying
27 expenses.
28 (e) The limited criminal history check requirement described in
29 subsection (a)(2) may be satisfied by fulfilling the components of an
30 expanded criminal history check under IC 20-26-2-1.5 and is subject
31 to the conditions described in IC 16-27-2-4(c).
32 (f) A person may not be registered under subsection (a) if the
